    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-02T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-02T14:00:00-05:00" n="819"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d819">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/912</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SFJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-02T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 23, 3 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d819fn1">Not printed.</note> In December
                    last arranged with Compañía Transatlántica and Compañía Pinillos Lines to
                    continue regular services on basis of taking only cargo approved by War Trade
                    Board. Later Compañía Transatlántica signed bunker form B–4, which provides all
                    their vessels abide by Bureau of Transportation General Rules No. 1,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d819fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_946">p. 946</ref>.</note> of
                    which clause (<hi rend="italic">l</hi>), paragraph 5, requires approval War
                    Trade Board to all voyages. See Journal No. 5. No new arrangements since
                    then.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
